-	 Contributing to train environmental engineers able to interact with other professionals in analysing and developing spatial plans.
Expected Learning Objectives (ELO). Upon completion of this course, students will be able to:
1.	Understand the structure and content of a variety of spatial planning instruments;
2.	Understand the operational stages of the planning process and critically evaluate its quality;
3.	Identify and analyze the main information on the biophysical and human environment of a geographical context, particularly with reference to contemporary environmental sustainability issues;
4.	Apply methodologies to support the formulation of ecological planning interventions, through the use of appropriate analytical tools;
5.	Understand and apply the key principles of Environmental Impact Assessment.

